21/03/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Four workers died and five were injured in a blast Thursday (March 20th) inside a hydroelectric power plant in the Anatolian province of Kahramanmaras.
Provincial Governor Mehmet Niyazi Tanilir said an investigation is under way into the cause of the explosion.
Authorities recently launched broad safety inspections after a string of fatal accidents at shipyards in Istanbul.
(BBC, Reuters, Zaman - 20/03/08)
